# Search Strategies

Master-level techniques for finding information that others miss.

## Search Operator Mastery

### Google Advanced Operators

| Operator | Purpose | Example |
|----------|---------|---------|
| `"exact phrase"` | Match exact words in order | `"supply chain disruption"` |
| `site:` | Search within specific domain | `site:gov climate data` |
| `-` | Exclude term | `apple -fruit -cider` |
| `OR` | Either term | `CEO OR "chief executive"` |
| `*` | Wildcard for unknown words | `"* is the new *"` |
| `filetype:` | Specific file format | `filetype:pdf annual report` |
| `intitle:` | Term in page title | `intitle:methodology` |
| `inurl:` | Term in URL | `inurl:research` |
| `before:` / `after:` | Date range | `after:2024-01-01` |
| `related:` | Similar sites | `related:reuters.com` |
| `cache:` | Google's cached version | `cache:example.com/page` |
| `define:` | Dictionary definition | `define:epistemology` |

### Operator Combinations

```text
# Find PDFs from government sites about a topic
site:gov filetype:pdf "climate change" "annual report"

# Find academic discussions excluding Wikipedia
"machine learning" site:edu -site:wikipedia.org

# Find recent news from specific sources
"company name" (site:reuters.com OR site:bloomberg.com) after:2025-01-01

# Find presentations and slide decks
"topic" (filetype:ppt OR filetype:pptx OR filetype:pdf) "slide"

# Find data files
"dataset name" (filetype:csv OR filetype:xlsx OR filetype:json)
```

